<TITLE>China-Shadow Puppet Show</TITLE>


<TEXT>
Tourists who <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">go</EVENT> to the Taishan Mountain of Tai'an, east China's Shandong Province, during the <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2017-SP">Spring</TIMEX3> Festival will be lucky to <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE">have</EVENT> the opportunity to <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">watch</EVENT> shadow puppet performances, an intangible cultural heritage of China. 

Dozens of classic traditional Chinese stories are <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">staged</EVENT>. 

The audience could also <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE">control</EVENT> the shadow puppets themselves to <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">experience</EVENT> the fun. 

"It's nice and funny. I <EVENT eid="e7" class="I_STATE">like</EVENT> it very much!" <EVENT eid="e8" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT> a little boy. 

"We can have contact with the traditional Chinese culture and <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">feel</EVENT> our intangible cultural heritage in the playing. It is an edutainment activity," <EVENT eid="e10" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT> a tourist. 

Shadow <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">puppet</EVENT>, which is made from animal skin or paperboard into the shape of human beings. When the show is <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">performing</EVENT>, the puppets are controlled by artists behind a white curtain, accompanied by local folk narration and melodies played by percussion and string instruments.
</TEXT>


